A man received multiple stab wounds in a feud between a shopper and a shop owner over Rs. 50 at Pina Vemali in Vizianagaram mandal in the wee hours of Tuesday. According to Rural CI A. Ravi Kumar, Nagaraju of Madhurawada in Visakhapatnam, who visited his relatives at the village, purchased some essentials on Monday at the shop owned by M. Appala Narayana. A wordy duel ensued during transaction. Around midnight, Nagaraju again visited the shop where Appala Narayana and his uncle Adi Narayana slept in the open and attacked them with a butcherâ€™s knife. While Adi Narayana received a grievous cut, Appala Narayana suffered multiple injuries.One of thetwo suffers multiple stab wounds inthe assault